@NODE "Introduction"

The fantastic Retina Blanker is a screenblanker created for the lucky 
persons who own a Retina Graphics board or card (whatever)!

The fact is that this is just a normal blanker except that it opens a 
screen directly on the board and displays a nice spliner. Very nice 
indeed!

NB: Do yourself a favour and read this damn document, it is not very 
long - and this is not just an ordinary screen blanker.

Why should I use this shit?
1:	Look at the size!! The first hunk of the file is the hunk that does 
the boring message replying, tooltype reading and shit like that, but the 
program throws this part off when it's loaded. So in Memory it only 
take up 1740 bytes + the stack size. Now you can ask yourself one 
question.... is 1740 bytes much?
2:	It is very fast and written in 100% asm 020+ to get an efficient 
optimized lightning speed proggy that takes up no memory.
3:	Runs as Commodity.
4:	Uses VERY little cpu speed when running in the background.
5:	I wrote it! -about 850 lines of code.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Requirements"

If you had payed attention in the introduction you already know by 
now, that this program require the following:
-A retina GFX board (such as my ZII from MacroSystem).
-A 020+ processor because of some special instructions and some non-
word alignments. I could naturally write a 68000 version, but since none 
really has a nothing but a 68000 anymore, I didn't want to waste time 
on it, but if enough people ask me (n>10) I just might do it.

And by the way. You use this program at you own risk and dont 
blame me if it fucks up your computer. It works excellent at my place 
and during all the tests. I take no responsibility at all.


                This program is only tested on my computer:

                           A2000, ECS, 1MB chip
                    4MB 16 bit fast/ 4MB 32 bit gvp sim
                           GVP 680EC30/882 40Mhz
                      120MB Quantum/ 440 Seagate SCSI
                    Retina ZII graphics board/ 4MB RAM

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Usage"
There is one good way to use this program and one bad. The good 
way is to put it in your Wbstartup and you dont have to worry about 
a thing. If you run it from the CLI it still autodetatches, but you cant 
use parameters because it reads the parameters from its icon and it has 
to run from workbench or from the Wbstartup in order to do so. If 
you run from the CLI it only uses default values.

So put it in your Wbstartup - the tooltypes means the following:

WAIT
This tooltype tells the blanker whether to blank or not when the time 
(BLANKDELAY) has run out. If this tooltype is set as WAIT without 
parentheses around it the blanker never blanks!!

RUN_PRI
Normally the blanker runs in the background with a low priority as -50, 
but when the blanker  starts its spliner you have to opportunity to 
decide what the priority should be (a byte value) -the default is 0.

WIDTH and HEIGHT
These two tooltypes together shows the blanker what resolution to use 
when running the spliner. These parameters are passed right to the 
library, so you better know what you're doing. The blanker finds out 
what default monitor setting (scan stuff ID) you run and opens the 
screen using this ID. The default values are 800 and 600.

LINES
This is obviously the number of lines the spliner uses when it runs. the 
default value is 450 (word value)
BLANKDELAY
This is the number of seconds before the blanker starts if no 
movement of either keyboard, mouse joystick has taken place. The 
default value is 300 seconds (=5 minutes) (longword value).

LINEDELAY
This is the delay between every drawn line on the screen. This delay is 
sort of an cpu cycle waster. To my knowledge there is no library time 
delay routine that delays less than 1/50 or 1/60 of a second. Therefore 
this parameter is dependent on how fast your processor is. If you have 
a 40Mhz 030 like me you might not want to set it below 5000 (which 
is default).
If any coders out there knows how to make a microsecond delay 
routine that gives the cpu time back to the system without wasting it 
- please tell me!!

MIN_VECTOR and MAX_VECTOR
The spliner is dependent on a random initialization routine. See, the 
spliner operates on little dots following precalculated vectors. The 
random values is chose from the difference between MIN_VECTOR 
and MAX_VECTOR. It is therefore important in order to get a 
diversed and random spliner every time the blanker starts, to set the 
values with a reasonable difference between them. The default is 1 and 
5. The minimum difference is 2 (3 and 5 eg.). These numbers actually 
describes the potential distance between the lines plottet on the screen.
@ENDNODE


@NODE "History"

1.0:
This is the first official release of the nice Retina Blanker.
There is no known bugs except for the lag of error messages, but 
that can hardly be considered as a bug. Who needs errormessages if 
everything is ok anyway :-) This program is very "mute" if something 
is wrong, - it won't say a thing! My X-girlfriend never got this idea 
quite right!!!

@ENDNODE


